data.title: Robovetter: Automatic vetting of Threshold Crossing Events (TCEs)
data.name: kepler-robovetter

evidence: "The DR25 Kepler Robovetter is a robotic decision-making code that dispositions each Threshold Crossing Event (TCE) from the Kepler pipeline into Planet Candidates (PCs) and False Positives (FPs)."
"To compile the code, use your available C++ compiler..." and run as a standalone executable (e.g., `./robovet ...`), indicating an end-user application rather than a library.

"The DR25 Robovetter code is provided, along with the necessary input files... and the resultant output files, so that users may validate their implementation." (code and data provided directly in the repo, with instructions to compile and run from source).
